title.narrative: ENHANCED GOUVERNMENT CAPACITY

description.narrative: Government capacity for health and nutrition coordination, planning, implementation, monitoring and evaluation is enhanced., which contributes to Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, children and women, especially the most vulnerable and hard-to-reach, utilise more quality essential health and nutrition services and benefit from positive health and nutrition care practices.

title.narrative: Government capacity for health and nutrition coordination, planning, implementation, monitoring and evaluation is enhanced.

description.narrative: Strengthening the capacity of the Government remains a priority for UNICEF to ensure an environment conducive to the implementation of key high-impact interventions and to make the health system resilient in the event of health emergencies. Several national strategic documents, including health and nutrition investment cases, have been developed or reviewed and validated since. As a result, the Government’s immunization budget has significantly increased from $400,000 to $1 million over the past two fiscal years. Also, the government is currently strongly committed to the fight against all forms of malnutrition, placing nutrition at the highest level on the country&39;s agenda. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/01/2022
